translated: Fritz, Carl Axel Gösta, MD, Nässjö, b. 18/12/08 in Nässjö to supervisor Albert F. and Lovisa Gustafsson. Married in 1938 to Maj Sundberg. Children: Margareta b. 1940, Sten b. 1943, Kerstin b. 1946. Completed high school in Lund in 1929, graduated with a degree in medicine in Lund in 1935, and became a licensed medical practitioner in Stockholm in 1940. Worked as a substitute assistant physician at Maria Hospital in Stockholm in 1940, assistant physician and temporary substitute physician at Umeå Hospital medical department from 1941-1942, assistant physician at Sahlgr. Hospital surgical department in 1943, temporary substitute physician at Carlanderska sanatorium in Gothenburg in 1943, temporary substitute physician at a sanatorium in Eksjö in 1943, and an attending physician at Nässjö Hospital from 1944-1946. Became a practicing physician in Nässjö from 1947 onwards. Serves as a board member of AB Nässjö Vaddfabriker and AB J.E. Sundberg & Son in Nässjö.
